text:
e="preserve">Paul Cronin (8 July 1938 – 13 September 2019) was an Australian actor. He was known for his roles in the Australian television series "Matlock Police" and "The Sullivans". He won the Silver Logie five times. Cronin was born in Jamestown, South Australia.
Cronin died on 13 September 2019 in Melbourne at the age of 81.
